5. Code of Conduct
You agree to comply with the following (“Code of Conduct”): Comply with the terms and conditions of third-party mobile platform providers, such as Apple and Google, from whom you download Devsisters Services, including the terms regarding payment for In-App purchases made through the platform;
Not to, in any circumstances, attempt to access or obtain other users’ account or login information;
Not use cheats, exploits, hacks, automation software, bots, mods or any unauthorized third-party software to modify, interfere or disrupt the Services;
Not develop, distribute, or publicly inform other users of “auto” software programs, “macro” software programs, or other “cheat utility” software programs or applications in violation of the Terms of Service;
Not exploit, distribute, or publicly inform other users of any game error, miscue, or bug which gives an unintended advantage;
Not disrupt, overburden, aid or assist in the attempt to modify, interfere or disrupt the Service or any other Service-related environment;
Not institute, assist or become involved in any type of attack, including, without limitation. distributing viruses or other attempts to disrupt the Service or any other user’s use of the Service;
Not send, post, transmit, or make available any material and/or information that may be abusive, threatening, illegal, obscene, defamatory, libelous, or containing nudity, excessive violence, or racially, religiously, sexually or otherwise objectionable or offensive;
Not create a false identity or impersonate another person or entity, including, without limitation, identities falsely indicating that you are Devsisters Corp. official or representative, message board or community board moderator, another user or host, and/or that you are a celebrity or public figure;
Through the Service, not make available any material or information that infringes upon any copyright, trademark, patent, trade secret, rights of privacy, rights of publicity or other rights of any persons or entities;
Not to harass, abuse, threaten or bully any other player or Devsisters employees, including Devsisters customer service representatives;
Not attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service, accounts registered or others, or to networks from which portions of the Service are provided, including circumventing or modifying, attempting to circumvent or modify, or assisting or encouraging any other person to circumvent or modify any security, technology, device, or software that is part of the Service;
Not engage in attempts to modify, reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decipher or otherwise try to derive the source code for any underlying software and/or other intellectual property used to provide the any or all of Devsisters Services;
Not to buy, sell, trade, or advertise to sell any virtual currency, items or game accounts for commercial purposes;
Not improperly use Devsisters support services, including by submitting false reports; Unless permitted by law or the existence and application of open source licenses, you will not modify, reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decipher or otherwise try to derive the source code for any underlying software or other intellectual property used to provide the Service or any Devsisters game;
Failure to comply with this Code of Conduct may result in suspending or revoking your account, where Devsisters reserves the right to determine which conduct is considered a violation and reserves the right to take action as needed.
